      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A mandated minimum wage increase will inevitably raise your operating costs, which is a direct hit to small businesses like yours. These higher labor costs will force you to either absorb the expense, which cuts into your profit margin, or pass the cost onto your customers through higher prices. In a rural area, this price increase is particularly noticeable and can directly impact local consumer spending. Therefore, the best approach is to actively seek ways to increase efficiency rather than relying on wage hikes.",
      "source": "target",
